Show Kodi current state:ph_check_app_name -s -a Kodi | more
Show Kodi run account:ph_get_app_user Kodi
Start or switch to Kodi:startkodi.sh | more
Stop Kodi:stopkodi.sh force | more
Restart Kodi:restartkodi.sh | more
Install Kodi and integrate with PieHelper:confapps_ph.sh -p inst -a Kodi
Remove Kodi from PieHelper and uninstall:confapps_ph.sh -p rem -a Kodi
Update Kodi to the latest version (only if installed as a package):ph_update_pkg $PH_KODI_PKG_NAME | more
Configure Kodi:confapps_ph.sh -p conf -a Kodi
Go to the OptsManagement for Kodi submenu:ph_show_menu OptsManagement_Kodi
Go to the TTYManagement for Kodi submenu:ph_show_menu TTYManagement_Kodi
Go to Main menu:ph_show_menu Main
Go to Apps menu:ph_show_menu Apps
Open Shell to home directory (Type 'CTRL-D' to return):cd;/bin/bash
Return to previous screen:return
